{
  "text": "When cell-cultured virus was held at 20 °C, a 4 log reduction in virus titre was observed within the first 26 days. After 46 days, titres were just above the detection limit, implying a 5 log-reduction. At 4 °C a decrease of 2-3 logs over 46 days was observed. No differences were observed when cell-cultured virus was diluted in guinea pig serum [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "12528856"
